%20knew%20this%20would%20never%20happen%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20didn't%20always%20like%20it%20but%20that%20is%20the%20process%20of%20being%20a%20parent.%20They're%20not%20supposed%20to%20like%20everything%20you%20do.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldberg%2C%20who%20became%20a%20mother%20to%20her%20only%20child%20Alex%20Martin%20in%201973%20when%20she%20was%2018%20years%20old%2C%20said%20she%20always%20traveled%20with%20her%20daughter%20when%20she%20went%20on%20tour.%20Martin%20would%20sit%20in%20the%20theater%20with%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECo-host%20Sunny%20Hostin%20also%20weighed%20in%20on%20the%20debate%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20think%20that%20you%20do%20have%20to%20prioritize%20certain%20things.%20You%20can't%20have%20everything%20all%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20You%20can%20have%20it%20at%20different%20times.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20career%20has%20suffered%2C%20I%20think%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20my%20children%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldberg%20made%20her%20name%20in%20Hollywood%20by%20starring%20in%20films%20like%20%26quot%3BThe%20Color%20Purple%26quot%3B%20in%201985%2C%20%26quot%3BGhost%26quot%3B%20in%201990%20which%20she%20won%20an%20Oscar%20for%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BSister%20Act%26quot%3B%20in%201992.%20She%20has%20been%20a%20co-host%20for%20%26quot%3BThe%20View%26quot%3B%20since%202007.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard%20professor%20and%20Nobel%20Prize%20winner%20Claudia%20Goldin%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-pay-gap-motherhood-fatherhood-nobel-prize-harvard-economist-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20earnings%20gap%20between%20men%20and%20women%20still%20exists%20in%20high-income%20countries%20because%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bmotherhood%20penalty%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20idea%20that%20when%20women%20have%20children%20their%20hours%20and%20