JP%20and%20today%20I%20have%20been%20given%20such%20a%20big%20opportunity.%20I%20must%20say%20that%20this%20can%20be%20possible%20only%20in%20a%20party%20like%20the%20BJP%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Saini%20said%20in%20the%20State%20Assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20learnt%20everything%20from%20scratch%20from%20former%20Chief%20Minister%20Manohar%20Lal%20Khattar.%20I%20have%20learnt%20even%20the%20minutest%20things%20from%20him%20and%20how%20to%20maintain%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%20witnessed%20a%20swift%20change%20of%20government%20over%20the%20past%2048%20hours%2C%20with%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Manohar%20Lal%20Khattar%20and%20the%20entire%20cabinet%2C%20which%20included%20three%20from%20the%20JJP%2C%20quitting%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proximate%20cause%20of%20the%20break-up%20of%20Mr%20Khattar's%20government%20was%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20BJP-JJP%20alliance%2C%20which%20was%20formed%20after%20the%202019%20Assembly%20election%2C%20in%20which%20the%20former%20emerged%20as%20the%20single-largest%20party%20but%20fell%20six%20seats%20short%20of%20an%20outright%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Saini%20was%20chosen%20as%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20after%20the%20surprise%20resignation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20the%20assembly%20today%2C%20Mr%20Saini%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BManohar%20Lal%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bsaint%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20has%20given%20a%20lot%20to%20Haryana%2C%20strengthened%20it%20and%20it%20was%20his%20thinking%20that%20weaker%20sections%20and%20poor%20should%20get%20benefits%20at%20their%20doorsteps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaini%20said%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20launched%20the%20'Beti%20Bachao%2C%20Beti%20Padhao%20programme%20in%202015%20and%20added%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20the%20state%20took%20it%20as%20a%20pledge%20to%20ensure%20success%20of%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710323040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fbpdjkd8_nayab-singh-saini-haryana-chief-minister_625x300_12_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-haryana-chief-minister-clears-floor-test-day-after-bjp-jjp-alliance-ends-5230243%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20Haryana%20Chief%20Minister%20Nayab%20Saini%20cleared%20a%20floor%20test%20aimed%20at%20proving%20that%20BJP%20had%20majority%20status%20in%20the%20assembly%20even%20after%20breaking%20ties%20with%20Dushyant%20Chautala's%20JJP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-haryana-chief-minister-clears-floor-test-day-after-bjp-jjp-alliance-ends-5230243%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-haryana-chief-minister-clears-floor-test-day-after-bjp-jjp-alliance-ends-5230243%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-haryana-chief-minister-clears-floor-test-day-after-bjp-jjp-alliance-ends-5230243%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20homes%20your%20real-estate%20agent%20doesn't%20want%20you%20to%20see%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20being%20covered%20up%20with%20cloth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f0772c6080194819ff0651%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReal-estate%20agent%20commissions%20have%20barely%20budged%20over%20decades.%20Critics%20blame%20a%20shady%20practice%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bsteering.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAllevinatis%2FGetty%2C%20stuartbur%2FGetty%2C%20malerapaso%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20month%20of%202020%20should've%20been%20a%20happy%20time%20for%20real-estate%20agents.%20The%20catastrophe%20of%20the%20pandemic%20had%20turned%20into%20an%20improbable%20housing-market%20boom%2C%20as%20home%20sales%20reached%2014-year%20highs.%20But%20instead%20of%20celebrating%20their%20unexpectedly%20prosperous%20year%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20agents%20were%20pissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20private%20chats%20and%20message%20boards%2C%20they%20complained%20about%20new%20rules%20that%20would%20publicly%20expose%20their%20commissions.%20For%20homebuyers%2C%20the%20amount%20an%20agent%20gets%20paid%20has%20historically%20been%20out%20of%20sight%2C%20out%20of%20mind.%20But%20as%20part%20of%20a%20November%202020%20settlement%20between%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20and%20the%20industry's%20top%20trade%20group%2C%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%2C%20real-estate%20search%20sites%20like%20Zillow%20and%20Redfin%20would%20soon%20start%20publicizing%20exactly%20how%20much%20buyers'%20agents%20stood%20to%20collect%20on%20nearly%20every%20home%20for%20sale%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20real-estate%20agents%2C%20no%20topic%20is%20more%20sensitive%20than%20their%20commissions.%20In%20private%20comments%20at%20the%20time%2C%20screenshots%20of%20which%20were%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20agents%20revealed%20just%20how%20squeamish%20they%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20no%20one's%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20disgruntled%20agent%20commented%20in%20a%20private%20Facebook%20group.%20%26quot%3BDo%20we%20go%20around%20asking%20people%20how%20much%20they%20make%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomeone%20has%20it%20in%20for%20real%20estate%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20vitriol%2C%20a%20brave%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20I'll%20call%20Julie%20%E2%80%94%20applauded%20the%20move%2C%20suggesting%20it%20could%20help%20rid%20the%20industry%20of%20one%20of%20its%20dirty%20secrets%3A%20a%20sly%20tactic%20called%20steering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20America's%20convoluted%20home-sales%20system%2C%20the%20seller%20typically%20pays%20out%20agents%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20a%20transaction.%20The%20commission%20is%20baked%20into%20the%20home's%20final%20price%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20usually%20between%205%25%20and%206%25%20of%20the%20total%20%E2%80%94%20and%20split%20evenly%20between%20the%20buyer's%20and%20seller's%20agents.%20Technically%2C%20the%20seller%20can%20promise%20as%20little%20as%20%240%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agent%3B%20after%20all%2C%20why%20pay%20for%20someone%20you%20didn't%20hire%3F%20But%20there's%20a%20catch%3A%20Offer%20less%20than%20the%20going%20rate%2C%20and%20you%20risk%20getting%20the%20cold%20shoulder%20from%20other%20brokers%20and%20fewer%20eyeballs%20on%20your%20listing.%20Agents%20might%20steer%20their%20clients%20toward%20the%20homes%20that%20offer%20the%20standard%20commission%20and%20away%20from%20ones%20that%20don't.%20The%20practice%20screws%20over%20both%20sellers%2C%20who%20might%20miss%20out%20on%20offers%2C%20and%20buyers%2C%20who%20might%20unknowingly%20pass%20over%20their%20dream%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20or%20not%20people%20admit%20it%2C%20steering%20due%20to%20commission%20rate%20definitely%20happens%20and%20it%20is%20incredibly%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Julie%20wrote%20in%20a%20Facebook%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWrong%2C%26quot%3B%20someone%20else%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3Bor%20the%20real%20world%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteering%20is%20notoriously%20difficult%20to%20prove%20or%20quantify%2C%20but%20evidence%20of%20the%20practice%20can%20be%20found%20littered%20throughout%20the%20housing%20market.%20The%20extent%20of%20steering%20is%20a%20main%20point%20of%20contention%20in%20the%20multibillion-dollar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclass-action%20lawsuits%20over%20agent%20commissions%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20the%20plaintiffs%20say%20the%20threat%20of%20steering%20is%20a%20big%20reason%20commissions%20have%20barely%20budged%20over%20the%20years.%20Wendy%20Gilch%2C%20a%20consumer%20advocate%20who%20focuses%20on%20transparency%20in%20real%20estate%20with%20her%20company%2C%20Selling%20Later%2C%20likened%20this%20moment%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20reset%20button%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20great%20opportunity%20to%20start%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Gilch%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20know%20how%20much%20steering%20actually%20happens%2C%20mostly%20because%20a%20buyer%20might%20never%20know%20they%20were%20a%20victim%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20article%20in%20NAR's%20code%20of%20ethics%20says%20Realtors%20must%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20and%20promote%20the%20interests%20of%20their%20client%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20organization's%20official%20position%20can%20be%20summed%20up%20simply%3A%20Steering%20doesn't%20exist.%20It's%20a%20myth%2C%20the%20argument%20goes%2C%20created%20by%20those%20who%20want%20to%20dismantle%20the%20system%20and%20force%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20to%20pay%20their%20agents%20separately.%20But%20multiple%20agents%20told%20me%20there%20are%20all%20kinds%20of%20ways%20shady%20practitioners%20try%20to%20skirt%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20some%20agents%20might%20filter%20out%20listings%20with%20subpar%20commissions%20before%20passing%20along%20options%20to%20their%20clients.%20Or%20if%20they%20do%20show%20their%20client%20a%20house%2C%20they%20could%20insinuate%20that%20a%20low%20commission%20is%20a%20warning%20sign%20that%20the%20seller%20is%20hard%20to%20deal%20with%20or%20invent%20reasons%20the%20house%20isn't%20a%20good%20fit.%20They%20could%20also%20caution%20that%20if%20they're%20not%20getting%20their%20desired%20commission%20from%20the%20seller%2C%20they'll%20expect%20the%20buyer%20to%20make%20up%20the%20difference.%20Agents%20are%20within%20their%20rights%20to%20do%20that%2C%20but%20it%20can%20discourage%20a%20cash-strapped%20buyer%20from%20pursuing%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20a%20Realtor%20has%20to%20do%20is%20make%20a%20face%20about%20a%20house%20and%20they%20put%20a%20question%20in%20the%20buyer's%20mind%20as%20to%20whether%20or%20not%20it%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20put%20an%20offer%20in%20on%20a%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Doug%20Miller%2C%20a%20real-estate%20attorney%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20say%20the%20stickiness%20of%20the%20going%20commission%20rate%20is%20evidence%20of%20steering's%20ubiquity.%20The%20cut%20that's%20split%20between%20agents%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20deal%20has%20basically%20fluctuated%20between%205%25%20and%206%25%20of%20the%20total%20sale%20price%20since%20at%20least%201992%2C%20despite%20the%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20home-search%20technology%2C%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20agents%2C%20and%20huge%20differences%20in%20agents'%20experience%20and%20skill.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20greater%20numbers%20of%20agents%20have%20been%20fighting%20for%20clients%2C%20while%20technology%20has%20streamlined%20their%20jobs%20and%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20anyone%20to%20look%20up%20homes%20online.%20In%20a%20competitive%20market%2C%20critics%20say%2C%20you'd%20expect%20the%20price%20of%20agents'%20services%20to%20come%20down.%20But%20data%20from%20RealTrends%20indicates%20that%20in%202021%2C%20even%20as%20home%20prices%20were%20skyrocketing%20and%20agents%20were%20signing%20up%20en%20masse%2C%20the%20typical%20commission%20rate%20actually%20went%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4596391%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20roughly%20265%2C000%20listings%20on%20Redfin%20in%2034%20large%20metropolitan%20areas%20found%20that%2C%20in%20a%20typical%20market%2C%20more%20than%2085%25%20of%20listings%20offered%20the%20two%20most%20common%20commission%20rates%20for%20buyers'%20agents.%20In%20Austin%2C%20Houston%2C%20and%20Kansas%20City%2C%20Missouri%2C%20more%20than%2095%25%20of%20listings%20offered%20a%20commission%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agent%20of%203%25%20or%202.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20wondered%20whether%20buyers'%20agents%20might%20forward%20fewer%20low-commission%20listings%20to%20their%20clients%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20fewer%20page%20views%20on%20sites%20like%20Zillow%20and%20Redfin.%20They%20found%20that%2C%20all%20else%20being%20equal%2C%20low-commission%20listings%20received%20significantly%20fewer%20page%20views%20on%20Redfin%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20homes%20that%20offered%20agent%20payments%20just%20slightly%20below%20the%20going%20rate%20got%20fewer%20eyeballs.%20Homes%20with%20lower%20buyer-agent%20commissions%20also%20took%20longer%20to%20sell%20and%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20sell%20at%20all%20than%20those%20offering%20the%20standard%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgents%20I%20talked%20with%20stressed%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20honest%2C%20hardworking%20representatives%20who%20just%20want%20the%20best%20for%20their%20clients.%20I%20believe%20them.%20But%20there%20are%20also%20just%20lots%20of%20agents%20out%20there%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebar%20for%20entry%20into%20the%20industry%20is%20shockingly%20low%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20most%20states%2C%20getting%20a%20license%20to%20work%20as%20a%20real-estate%20agent%20requires%20paying%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%2C%20doing%20several%20weeks'%20worth%20of%20coursework%2C%20and%20passing%20a%20multiple-choice%20test.%20It's%20no%20surprise%2C%20then%2C%20that%20there%20are%20some%201.5%20million%20NAR%20members%2C%20or%20more%20than%20two%20Realtors%20for%20every%20available%20home%20on%20the%20market.%20And%20that%20doesn't%20even%20count%20all%20the%20agents%20who%20aren't%20members%20of%20the%20organization%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20about%201.3%20million%20licensees%20in%20the%20US%20who%20don't%20belong%20to%20the%20group%2C%20meaning%20they%20can't%20use%20the%20Realtor%20title%20and%20don't%20subscribe%20to%20its%20code%20of%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20low%20standards%20and%20lack%20of%20oversight%20can%20create%20hazardous%20conditions%20for%20buyers%20and%20sellers.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20now%20defunct%20discount%20brokerage%20Rex%20Real%20Estate%20released%20recordings%20of%20roughly%20600%20calls%20in%20which%20other%20agents%20vowed%20to%20avoid%20properties%20listed%20by%20Rex%20that%20offered%20less-than-satisfactory%20commissions.%20In%20one%20call%2C%20court%20documents%20say%2C%20a%20Keller%20Williams%20agent%20told%20a%20Rex%20representative%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20not%20offering%20any%20buyer's%20commission%2C%20then%20that's%20fine.%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20show%20that%20%5Bproperty%5D%2C%20and%20you're%20probably%20going%20to%20run%20into%20the%20same%20issue%20with%20everybody%20here.%26quot%3B%20Another%20ReMax%20agent%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20show%20a%20listing%20where%20I'm%20not%20guaranteed%20a%20commission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrendon%20Bowers%2C%20a%20former%20real-estate%20agent%20who%20spent%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20working%20as%20a%20branch%20manager%20for%20Rex%20in%20the%20Phoenix%20market%2C%20told%20me%20he%20encountered%20this%20sort%20of%20thing%20all%20the%20time.%20He%20said%20buyers'%20agents%20might%20call%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3B'Why%20is%20there%20no%20buyer's%20commission%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20I%20have%20to%20negotiate%20this%3F%20Nevermind%2C%20we're%20just%20going%20to%20go%20on%20to%20the%20next%20one.%26quot%3B%20Steering%2C%20he%20added%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20flat-out%20a%20part%20of%20real%20estate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20NAR%20told%20me%20that%20Rex%20was%20cherry-picking%20from%20thousands%20of%20calls%20and%20that%20these%20agents%20may%20have%20eventually%20shown%20their%20clients%20the%20homes%2C%20however%20begrudgingly.%20But%20even%20the%20mere%20%3Cem%3Ethreat%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20steering%20is%20enough%20to%20keep%20commissions%20from%20dropping%2C%20Stephen%20Brobeck%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%2C%20told%20me.%20The%20problem%20isn't%20that%20steering%20is%20rampant%2C%20Brobeck%20said%3B%20if%20most%20listings%20in%20a%20market%20already%20offer%20uniform%20commission%20rates%2C%20there's%20no%20need%20for%20an%20agent%20to%20steer%20their%20client%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20It's%20the%20fear%20of%20steering%20that%20maintains%20the%20system.%20A%20seller%20might%20hear%20of%20examples%20of%20steering%2C%20or%20get%20a%20warning%20from%20their%20agent%20of%20the%20risks%20involved%20in%20offering%20substandard%20commissions%2C%20and%20decide%20it's%20worth%20it%20just%20to%20promise%20the%20going%20rate.%20After%20all%2C%20everyone%20else%20is%20doing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EClass-action%20plaintiffs%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20have%20proposed%20something%20called%20decoupling%2C%20in%20which%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20just%20pay%20their%20agents%20separately%2C%20as%20a%20way%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20steering.%20The%20DOJ%20has%20argued%20that%20as%20long%20as%20sellers%20pay%20a%20commission%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agents%2C%20they'll%20be%20pressured%20to%20promise%20the%20going%20rate.%20In%20the%20proposed%20alternative%2C%20sellers%20would%20promise%20a%20commission%20only%20to%20their%20agent.%20For%20buyers%2C%20it%20would%20be%20more%20complicated%3B%20they'd%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20pay%20their%20agent%20directly%2C%20and%20how%20much.%20They%20could%20either%20pay%20the%20broker%20out%20of%20pocket%20or%20arrange%20to%20get%20a%20rebate%20from%20the%20seller%20once%20the%20deal%20closes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20changes%20could%20come%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%20With%20commissions%20under%20heightened%20scrutiny%2C%20more%20agents%20are%20getting%20buyers%20to%20sign%20buyer-broker%20representation%20contracts%20laying%20out%20the%20rate%20the%20agent%20expects%20to%20get%20paid%2C%20regardless%20of%20what%20the%20seller%20offers%20in%20the%20listing.%20If%20an%20agent%20wants%203%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price%20and%20the%20house%20you%20buy%20provides%20only%202%25%2C%20you%20might%20have%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20difference.%20If%20you're%20working%20with%20a%20good%20agent%2C%20that%20will%20probably%20feel%20worth%20it.%20But%20if%20sellers%20stop%20offering%20commissions%20altogether%2C%20buyers%20might%20have%20to%20make%20some%20tough%20choices.%20Many%20more%20buyers%20might%20choose%20to%20go%20it%20alone%20rather%20than%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket%20for%20an%20agent's%20services.%20Or%20they%20could%20pay%20their%20agents%20a%20flat%20fee%20or%20an%20hourly%20rate%20instead%20of%20a%20commission%2C%20though%20it's%20unclear%20how%20many%20agents%20would%20take%20that%20deal.%20Buyers%20might%20also%20start%20writing%20offers%20on%20homes%20that%20are%20contingent%20on%20making%20sure%20their%20agent%20gets%20paid%3A%20%26quot%3BI'll%20offer%20you%20%24400%2C000%20for%20your%20house%2C%20but%20you've%20got%20to%20give%20me%20back%20%2412%2C000%20so%20I%20can%20cut%20a%20check%20to%20my%20broker.%26quot%3B%20But%20there's%20still%20no%20guarantee%20that%20sellers%20would%20agree%20to%20that%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20hot%20market%20like%20the%20one%20we've%20seen%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NAR%20says%20decoupling%20would%20only%20heighten%20the%20inequalities%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%20Rich%20people%20could%20afford%20to%20get%20an%20agent%20and%20enjoy%20all%20the%20benefits%20that%20come%20with%20one%2C%20while%20poorer%20buyers%20might%20be%20left%20on%20their%20own.%20Others%20in%20favor%20of%20decoupling%20say%20the%20industry%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20get%20creative%20to%20ensure%20that%20as%20many%20buyers%20as%20possible%20could%20still%20access%20agents.%20Meanwhile%2C%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20would%20negotiate%20harder%20and%20maybe%20save%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20on%20a%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENobody%20expects%20agents%20to%20work%20for%20free%2C%20but%20the%20near%20uniformity%20of%20commission%20rates%20is%20strong%20evidence%20that%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20aren't%20bargaining%20nearly%20as%20much%20as%20they%20should%20be.%20If%20you're%20a%20buyer%2C%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20avoid%20falling%20victim%20to%20steering.%20Be%20wary%20of%20relying%20too%20much%20on%20an%20agent%20to%20feed%20you%20listings%3B%20it's%20worth%20doing%20your%20own%20research%2C%20too.%20On%20sites%20like%20Zillow%20and%20Redfin%2C%20you%20can%20often%20see%20the%20commission%20being%20offered%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agent.%20If%20a%20listing%20is%20offering%20less%20than%20what's%20typical%20in%20your%20area%20and%20your%20agent%20is%20acting%20weird%20about%20it%2C%20that%20might%20be%20a%20red%20flag.%20There%20are%20lots%20of%20willing%20brokers%20out%20there%3B%20if%20you%20suspect%20steering%2C%20agents%20told%20me%2C%20you've%20got%20plenty%20of%20options%20for%20a%20second%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20there%20are%20good%2C%20honest%20agents%20out%20there%20who%20deserve%20every%20penny%20of%20their%20commission.%20But%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20talk%20to%20many%20buyers%20to%20realize%20that%20not%20everyone%20meets%20that%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20called%20up%20Julie%2C%20the%20agent%20in%20the%20private%20Facebook%20group%20who%20spoke%20up%20about%20steering%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20She%20asked%20that%20I%20not%20use%20her%20real%20name%20because%20she%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20drawn%20into%20the%20controversy%20over%20commissions%20and%20all%20the%20lawsuits%20the%20NAR%20is%20facing%3B%20if%20things%20were%20tense%20back%20in%202020%2C%20they've%20only%20gotten%20more%20heated