iser.%20It%20allowed%20him%20to%20live%20his%20last%20few%20years%20stress-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Alexander%20faced%20many%20challenges%20since%20he%20was%20born%20in%201946.%20He%20endured%20the%20worst%20polio%20outbreak%20in%20US%20history%20with%20almost%2058%2C000%20cases%20-%20mostly%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20New%20York%20Post%20report%2C%20the%20disease%20severely%20affected%20Mr%20Alexander%2C%20requiring%20him%20to%20use%20a%20machine%20to%20breathe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolion%2C%20or%20Poliomyelitis%2C%20is%20a%20disabling%20and%20life-threatening%20disease%20caused%20by%20the%20poliovirus.%20The%20virus%20spreads%20from%20person%20to%20person%20and%20can%20infect%20a%20person's%20spinal%20cord%2C%20causing%20paralysis.%20It%20made%20Mr%20Alexander%20too%20weak%20to%20breathe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20underwent%20an%20emergency%20tracheotomy%20and%20was%20placed%20in%20an%20iron%20lung%20to%20help%20his%20body%20combat%20the%20deadly%20disease.%20He%20relied%20on%20the%20neck-to-toe%20machine%20to%20survive%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20iron%20lung%20employs%20a%20technique%20called%20%26quot%3Bfrog%20breathing%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20uses%20the%20throat%20muscles%20to%20force%20air%20past%20the%20vocal%20cords%2C%20allowing%20the%20patient%20to%20swallow%20oxygen%20one%20mouthful%20at%20a%20time%2C%20pushing%20it%20down%20the%20throat%20and%20into%20the%20lungs.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710322680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fov63bdd8_paul-alexander-polio-1200_625x300_01_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpolio-infected-man-who-spent-70-years-inside-an-iron-lung-dies-5230523%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Paul%20Alexander%20faced%20many%20challenges%20since%20he%20was%20born%20in%201946.%20He%20endured%20the%20worst%20polio%20outbreak%20in%20US%20history%20with%20almost%2058%2C000%20cases%20-%20mostly%20children.%22%2C%22author