ister%20responsible%20for%20the%20UK's%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20has%20told%20UK%20carmakers%20to%20check%20their%20supply%20chains%20after%20Sky%20News%20analysis%20suggested%20luxury%20models%20were%20finding%20their%20way%20to%20Moscow%20showrooms%20via%20ex-Soviet%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fminister-warns-uk-carmakers-as-sky-report-highlights-whack-a-mole-challenge-over-russia-sanctions-13093342%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fminister-warns-uk-carmakers-as-sky-report-highlights-whack-a-mole-challenge-over-russia-sanctions-13093342%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fminister-warns-uk-carmakers-as-sky-report-highlights-whack-a-mole-challenge-over-russia-sanctions-13093342%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Charts%3A%20Making%20Sense%20of%20Poor%20Learning%20Outcomes%20of%20Primary%20School%20Children%20in%20Tribal%20Districts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12194631%2FUntitled-design-39-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMumbai%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20Learning%20levels%20for%20primary%20school%20children%20in%20predominantly%20tribal%20districts%20were%20poor%20compared%20to%20neighbouring%20districts%20with%20lower%20tribal%20populations%2C%20an%C2%A0%3Cb%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0analysis%20of%20data%20from%20the%20Annual%20Status%20of%20Education%20Report%20(ASER)%202022%20across%20five%20states%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ideasforindia.in%2Ftopics%2Fhuman-development%2Fpersistent-struggle-for-learning-a-tale-of-tribal-regions.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20researchers%20from%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20Bombay%20(IIT-B)%20uses%20results%20of%20the%20National%20Achievement%20Survey%2C%202021%2C%20finding%20that%20learning%20levels%20for%20scheduled%20tribe%20(ST)%20children%20in%20grade%20V%20were%2053%25%20and%2041%25%20in%20mathematics%20and%20language%20tests%2C%20respectively.%20The%20corresponding%20national%20averages%20are%2055%25%20and%2044%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIncreased%20provision%20of%20infrastructure%20facilities%20in%20schools%20is%20necessary%2C%20yet%20not%20sufficient%20to%20improve%20the%20learning%20outcomes%20of%20children%20in%20these%20tribal%20regions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20study%20says.%20%E2%80%9C%5BO%5Dne%20of%20the%20most%20important%20aspects%20requiring%20attention%20is%20pedagogy.%20For%20instance%2C%20teachers%20need%20to%20capture%20the%20attention%20of%20students%20by%20making%20classroom%20teaching%20interesting%20as%20well%20as%20interactive%2C%20which%20can%20be%20done%20through%20the%20use%20of%20visual%20aids%2C%20games%20and%20real-world%20applications.%20Teachers%20also%20need%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20diverse%20learning%20styles%20and%20needs%20of%20students.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1657743%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAs%2520per%2520Census%25202011%252C%2520literacy%2C73%2525%2520at%2520all%2520India%2520level.%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%202017-18%20published%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20(MoSPI)%2C%20the%20literacy%20rate%20for%20STs%20is%2067.7%25%2C%20and%20the%20corresponding%20figure%20overall%20is%2076.9%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENationally%2C%20children%E2%80%99s%20basic%20reading%20ability%20has%20dropped%20to%20pre-2012%20levels%2C%20reversing%20the%20slow%20improvement%20achieved%20in%20the%20earlier%20years%2C%20shows%20the%20ASER%202022%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.asercentre.org%2Fdocs%2FASER%25202022%2520report%2520pdfs%2FAll%2520India%2520documents%2Faserreport2022.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20ASER%20provides%20information%20on%20the%20status%20of%20school%20education%20(enrollment%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20learning%20etc.)%20only%20for%20rural%20India.%20It%20does%20not%20provide%20information%20by%20social%20groups.%C2%A0%3Cb%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0used%20census%20data%20to%20categorise%20districts%20with%20a%20tribal%20population%20of%20more%20than%2050%25%20as%20%E2%80%98tribal%20districts%E2%80%99%20and%20those%20with%20less%20than%2050%25%20as%20%E2%80%98non-tribal%20districts%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20analysed%20the%20average%20learning%20outcomes%20for%20the%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EManipur%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Nagaland%20were%20selected%20due%20to%20their%20relatively%20poor%20infrastructure%20compared%20to%20other%20states%20with%20high%20tribal%20populations%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fudiseplus.gov.in%2F%23%2Fpage%2Fpublications%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUnified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20plus%202021-22%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(UDISE%2B).%20Odisha%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20had%20better%20infrastructure%20such%20as%20electricity%2C%20water%2C%20sanitation%20and%20hygiene%2C%20and%20yet%20had%20poor%20learning%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EPoor%20facilities%20responsible%20for%20poor%20outcomes%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ELack%20of%20basic%20infrastructure%20usually%20translates%20to%20poor%20learning%20outcomes.%20For%20example%2C%2037%25%20of%20government%20schools%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%2046%25%20in%20Nagaland%20do%20not%20have%20drinking%20water%20facilities%20within%20the%20school%20premises%2C%20according%20to%20UDISE%2B.%20Similarly%2C%2037%25%20government%20schools%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%2030%25%20in%20Nagaland%2C%20and%2029%25%20in%20Manipur%20do%20not%20have%20functional%20girls%E2%80%99%20toilets%20within%20the%20school%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%229f21eb94-8d14-4bac-9ee8-e65c9134505b%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22Details%20On%20Infrastructure%20Facilities%2C%202021-2022%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CLearning%20outcomes%20are%20directly%20linked%20to%20the%20environment%20in%20which%20a%20student%20is%20studying%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Protiva%20Kundu%2C%20Research%20Lead%20and%20Thematic%20Lead%20%E2%80%93%20Social%20Sectors%2C%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Budget%20and%20Governance%20Accountability%20(CBGA).%20%E2%80%9CThe%20presence%20of%20basic%20infrastructure%20in%20schools%2C%20like%20adequate%20classrooms%2C%20toilets%2C%20water%2C%20sanitation%20and%20hygiene%20(WASH)%20facilities%2C%20and%20playgrounds%20creates%20an%20enabling%20environment%20for%20the%20student%E2%80%99s%20learning.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20ASER%20data%2C%20the%20three%20states%20exhibit%20low%20learning%20levels.%20At%20the%20primary%20level%2C%20reading%20outcomes%20stand%20at%2023.1%25%20for%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%2049.8%25%20for%20Manipur%2C%20and%2034.3%25%20for%20Nagaland.%20Similarly%2C%20mathematics%20outcomes%20are%2049.2%25%20for%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%2069.9%25%20for%20Manipur%2C%20and%2047.0%25%20for%20Nagaland.%20These%20figures%20vary%20from%20the%20national%20averages%20of%2055%25%20in%20reading%20and%2044%25%20in%20mathematics%20(Data%20from%20some%20districts%20are%20missing).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20basic%20components%20are%20in%20place%2C%20such%20as%20drinking%20water%2C%20separate%20and%20functional%20toilets%2C%20classrooms%20that%20do%20not%20leak%2C%20you%20do%20not%20require%20smart%20classrooms%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Priya%20Nadkarni%2C%20founder%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmrida.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMrida%20Education%20and%20Welfare%20Society%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20non-profit%20based%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20that%20provides%20vocational%2C%20career%2C%20and%20skills%20training%20to%20middle%20grade%20and%20high%20school%20tribal%20student.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20a%20certain%20extent%2C%20there%20is%20a%20relationship%20as%2C%20if%20these%20facilities%20are%20absent%2C%20children%20won%E2%80%99t%20attend%20school.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22c94bfa17-7c53-44ee-b575-cfc83e423af1%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22District-wise%20Tribal%20Population%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Learning%20Outcomes%20For%20Manipur%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%223d053ba4-c389-4411-88db-cc65c83e0e5b%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22District-wise%20Tribal%20Population%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Learning%20Outcomes%20For%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%225ace4ddf-03a6-409d-8ae2-7e5235ac8dcb%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22District-wise%20Tribal%20Population%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Learning%20Outcomes%20For%20Nagaland%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOverall%2C%20learning%20levels%20in%20districts%20of%20these%20three%20northeastern%20states%20are%20lower%20than%20the%20national%20average.%20It%20appears%20that%20there%20is%20little%20difference%20between%20the%20learning%20outcomes%20in%20the%20tribal%20and%20non-tribal%20districts%2C%20but%20the%20districts%20for%20which%20data%20are%20missing%20have%20tribal%20populations%20of%2070%25%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EChhattisgarh%20and%20Odisha%20see%20low%20learning%20outcomes%20despite%20WASH%20facilities%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAlthough%20electricity%20and%20WASH%20facilities%20are%20available%20in%20many%20tribal%20districts%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Odisha%2C%20this%20access%20to%20infrastructure%20has%20yet%20to%20translate%20into%20better%20learning%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20UDISE%2B%20data%2C%20drinking%20water%20facilities%20are%20available%20in%2098.4%25%20government%20schools%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20functional%20toilets%20in%2097.6%25%20schools.%20In%20Odisha%2C%20the%20coverage%20is%2097%25%20for%20drinking%20water%20facilities%20and%2096.4%25%20for%20functional%20toilets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EYet%2C%20learning%20outcomes%20in%20Chattisgarh%20stand%20at%2040.1%25%20in%20reading%20and%2034.5%25%20in%20mathematics%20at%20the%20primary%20level%2C%20while%20in%20Odisha%2C%20they%20are%2041.6%25%20and%2040.3%25%20respectively.%20The%20average%20learning%20outcomes%20for%20reading%20and%20mathematics%20in%20tribal%20districts%20are%2030.7%25%20and%2027.07%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%2017.12%25%20and%2018.73%25%20respectively%20in%20Odisha%2C%20far%20below%20the%20state%20averages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%224102a31b-06ad-4c79-910c-883d1ce294a2%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22District-wise%20Tribal%20Population%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Learning%20Outcomes%20For%20Chhattisgarh%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EChhattisgarh%20fares%20poorly%20overall%20in%20learning%20outcomes%20for%20both%20reading%20and%20mathematics.%20However%2C%20districts%20such%20as%20Narayanpur%20and%20Bijapur%2C%20which%20have%20a%20tribal%20population%20of%20almost%2080%25%2C%20fare%20the%20worst.%20Most%20tribal%20districts%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20have%20relatively%20poor%20learning%20outcomes%20compared%20to%20the%20non-tribal%20districts.%20Among%20non-tribal%20districts%2C%20Koriya%20and%20Korba%20which%20fare%20the%20worst%20have%20a%20tribal%20population%20of%2046.1%25%20and%2040.6%25%2C%20respectively.%20Except%20for%20Uttar%20Bastar%20Kanker%2C%20all%20of%20the%20tribal%20districts%20have%20learning%20outcomes%20below%20the%20state-wide%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22b1436ff0-b1ff-459f-aca4-a0c815be54ee%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22District-wise%20Tribal%20Population%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Learning%20Outcomes%20For%20Odisha%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0has%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20education%20departments%20in%20the%20five%20states%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20learning%20outcomes%2C%20infrastructural%20facilities%20and%20teaching%20approaches.%20We%20will%20update%20this%20story%20when%20we%20receive%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ELack%20of%20qualified%20teachers%20and%20poor%20pupil-teacher%20ratios%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CInfrastructure%20is%20a%20critical%20input%20for%20learning%20outcomes%20as%20it%20helps%20create%20a%20conducive%20learning%20environment%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kundu%20of%20CBGA.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%20there%20are%20many%20other%20determinants%20which%20influence%20learning%20outcomes%2C%20such%20as%20teacher-student%20ratio%2C%20professionally%20qualified%20teachers%2C%20availability%20of%20textbooks%2C%20the%20language%20of%20textbooks%2C%20mode%20of%20teaching%2C%20socio-economic%20condition%20of%20the%20students%2C%20parents%E2%80%99%20livelihoods%2C%20parents%E2%80%99%20income%2C%20distance%20to%20schools%20etc.%20These%20are%20particularly%20important%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20tribal%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0analysed%20the%20district-wise%20qualification%20of%20primary%20teachers%20and%20pupil-teacher%20ratios%20in%20Odisha%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22b9b98c88-26e2-4dae-9eb0-a20d9f542782%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22Qualification%20Of%20Teachers%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Pupil-Teacher%20Ratio%20In%20Primary%20Classes%20(I-IV)%20In%20Odisha%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Education%20has%20recommended%20a%20pupil-teacher%20ratio%20for%20regular%20school%20at%2010%3A1%20for%20the%20primary%20level%20and%2015%3A1%20for%20the%20upper%20primary%2C%20secondary%20and%20higher%20secondary%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20primary%20classes%20of%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20tribal%20districts%2C%20an%20almost%20equal%20proportion%20of%20teachers%20have%20a%20graduate%20qualification%2C%20and%20a%20higher%20secondary%20or%20below%20qualification.%20Districts%20such%20as%20Malkangiri%2C%20Nabarangpur%2C%20and%20Sundargarh%20have%20the%20least%20percentage%20of%20teachers%20with%20a%20graduate%20qualification.%20They%20also%20have%20a%20significant%20tribal%20population.%20In%20the%20non-tribal%20districts%20in%20Odisha%2C%20almost%20all%20districts%20have%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20teachers%20with%20a%20graduate%20qualification.%20Naupada%20and%20Kalahandi%20districts%20have%20a%20proportion%20of%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20teachers%20with%20a%20graduate%20degree%2C%20but%20they%20exhibit%20significantly%20higher%20tribal%20populations%20of%2029%25%20and%2033%25%2C%20they%20also%20have%20significantly%20lower%20learning%20outcomes%20in%20both%20English%20and%20mathematics%20compared%20to%20the%20other%20%E2%80%98non-tribal%E2%80%99%20districts.%20The%20districts%20with%20a%20significantly%20high%20proportion%20of%20graduate-qualified%20teachers%20have%20the%20least%20tribal%20population%2C%20at%20less%20than%2010%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22d613a0b7-0c53-4835-b48e-faa06220e4f3%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22interactive%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22Qualification%20Of%20Teachers%20%26amp%3Bamp%3B%20Pupil-Teacher%20Ratio%20In%20Primary%20Classes%20(I-IV)%20In%20Chhattisgarh%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20most%20tribal%20districts%20have%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20primary%20teachers%20with%20a%20graduate%20qualification.%20Among%20non-tribal%20districts%2C%20all%20districts%20have%2060%25%20or%20more%20teachers%20with%20graduate%20qualifications%20except%20Koriya%20(56.7%25)%20which%20has%20a%20tribal%20population%20of%2046%25.%20Koriya%20also%20sees%20poor%20learning%20outcomes%20among%20the%20non-tribal%20districts.%20The%20variations%20in%20pupil-teacher%20ratios%20are%20greater%20for%20tribal%20districts.%20Narayanpur%20and%20Bijapur%20which%20had%20the%20lowest%20learning%20outcomes%20in%20the%20state%20also%20have%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20graduate-qualified%20teachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ETeaching%20approaches%20and%20partnership%20programmes%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ELearning%20levels%20depend%20on%20the%20organisation%20of%20the%20teaching-learning%20process%2C%20as%20the%20IIT-B%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPratham%20has%20evolved%20a%20solution%20called%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pratham.org%2Fabout%2Fteaching-at-the-right-level%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETeaching%20at%20the%20Right%20Level%20(TaRL)%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0which%20enables%20children%20to%20acquire%20foundational%20skills%20like%20reading%20and%20arithmetic%20quickly.%20Regardless%20of%20age%20or%20grade%2C%20teaching%20starts%20at%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20level%20and%20is%20targeted%20to%20children%20who%20have%20already%20reached%20grade%20III%2C%20IV%20or%20V%20but%20have%20still%20not%20acquired%20basic%20skills.%20The%20focus%20is%20on%20helping%20children%20with%20basic%20reading%2C%20understanding%2C%20as%20well%20as%20arithmetic%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20TaRL%20approach%20is%20implemented%20in%20two%20ways%E2%80%93directly%20by%20Pratham%20instructors%20through%20%E2%80%9CLearning%20Camps%E2%80%9D%20or%20as%20part%20of%20a%20Pratham-government%20partnership%20programme%20where%20government%20teachers%20implement%20TaRL%20as%20part%20of%20the%20school%20day.%20In%20the%20direct%20model%2C%20Pratham%20instructors%20run%20three%20to%20five%20camps%20of%2010%20days%20each%2C%20for%20about%20three%20hours%20a%20day.%20In%20the%20partnership%20model%2C%20government%20teachers%20use%20this%20approach%20over%20a%20longer%20period%20in%20the%20school%20year%20(four%20to%20six%20months)%20with%20a%20dedicated%20time%20of%20one%20to%20two%20hours%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhen%20Pratham%20partnered%20with%20the%20Government%20of%20Karnataka%20in%202017%2C%20letters%20could%20only%20be%20read%20by%2016%25%20of%20students%2C%20words%20by%2023%25%2C%20paragraphs%20by%2023%25%2C%20and%20an%20entire%20story%20by%20only%2029%25.%20Additionally%2C%20division%20could%20only%20be%20performed%20by%2031%25%2C%20multiplication%20by%2049%25%2C%20subtraction%20by%2066%25%2C%20and%20addition%20by%2079%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20project%20in%202018%2C%20an%20entire%20story%20could%20be%20read%20by%2065%25%20of%20the%20students.%20The%20ability%20to%20perform%20mathematical%20operations%20increased%20to%2069%25%20in%20division%2C%2082%25%20in%20multiplication%2C%2093%25%20in%20subtraction%2C%20and%2097%25%20in%20addition.%20This%20project%20involved%20over%20450%2C000%20children%20in%20grades%20IV%20and%20V%20across%2017%2C000%20schools%20in%2013%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20need%20resourceful%20and%20motivated%20teachers%20who%20will%20use%20every%20situation%20to%20create%20learning%20opportunities%2C%E2%80%9D%20reflects%20Nadkarni.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20straightforward%20solution%20to%20improve%20learning%20outcomes.%E2%80%9D%20She%20believes%20that%20learning%20outcomes%20are%20a%20function%20of%20many%20factors%20beyond%20the%20classroom.%20These%20could%20be%20nutrition%2C%20access%20to%20school%2C%20culture%20within%20the%20community%2C%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20role%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20heterogeneous%20and%20the%20characteristics%20of%20students%20vary%20across%20class%2C%20caste%2C%20religion%2C%20gender%2C%20geographical%20presence%2C%20and%20economic%20status%2C%20and%20hence%20every%20student%20has%20varied%20needs%2C%E2%80%9D%20reflects%20Kundu%20from%20CBGA.%20%E2%80%9CAny%20uniform%20education%20policy%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20address%20the%20diversity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Feducation-check%2Fwhy-learning-outcomes-for-tribal-districts-are-poor-899171%5C%22%3Estory%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2F%5C%22%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3E%2C%20a%20data-driven%2C%20public-interest%20journalism%20non-profit%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710257739000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12194631%2FUntitled-design-39-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fin-charts-tracking-poor-learning-outcomes-for-primary-school-children-in-tribal-districts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Districts%20with%2050%25%20and%20more%20tribal%20populations%20see%20poor%20mathematics%20and%20English%20learning%20scores.%20While%20minimum%20infrastructure%20facilities%20are%20necessary%2C%20it%20is%20not%20enough%2C%20say%20experts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fin-charts-tracking-poor-learning-outcomes-for-primary-school-children-in-tribal-districts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UP%20Court%20Convicts%20Ten%20Men%20for%202018%20Lynching%20of%20Muslim%20Man%20on%20Fake%20Rumours%20of%20Cow%20Slaughter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F12203306%2FQasims-family.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Almost%20six%20years%20after%20Muslim%20goat-trader%20Qasim%20was%20lynched%20by%20a%20mob%20of%20Hindu%20men%20in%20a%20village%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Hapur%20on%20fabricated%20rumours%20of%20cow%20slaughter%2C%20a%20local%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2012)%20convicted%20ten%20persons%20for%20the%20brutal%20murder%20and%20sentenced%20them%20to%20life%20imprisonment%2C%20lawyers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQasim%2C%2045%2C%20was%20among%20the%20most%20prominent%20victims%20of%20state-induced%20hate%20crimes%20in%20the%20name%20of%20cow%20slaughter%20in%20UP%20after%20the%20infamous%20Dadri%20incident%20in%202015%2C%20when%20a%20Muslim%20man%20named%20Mohammad%20Akhlaque%20was%20beaten%20to%20death%20over%20rumours%20of%20killing%20a%20cow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQasim%20was%20beaten%20to%20death%20near%20the%20fields%20of%20Bajhera%20Khurd%20village%20under%20the%20Pilkhuwa%20police%20station%20in%20Hapur%20on%20June%2016%2C%202018%2C%20a%20year%20after%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20came%20to%20power%20in%20the%20state%20and%20provided%20moral%20backing%20to%20violent%20cow%20protectionism%20and%20vigilantism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20one%20of%20the%20main%20accused%20in%20the%20Hapur%20lynching%20had%20even%20bragged%20about%20his%20role%20after%20he%20was%20released%20from%20jail%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20victims%E2%80%99%20families%20insisted%20that%20the%20allegations%20